h":"0081828dec9051eaed4fb112f4c512500cc687cf0388ef58f49f8c45d15d4510","event_uuid":"830eddff-d796-4ed2-9a91-3c56649f47c4","position":{"commit_sha":"45bf19579ecc3a4fcbe1dc4623be01a5267e68c8","position":"1784453197910482975-830eddff-d796-4ed2-9a91-3c56649f47c4"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416836736349001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"e02894f9-a982-48a4-8382-995a6f50ce05","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"3275-b164-2e9b-4e66"}],"description":"## What\nOne-time backfill of the complexity and clone-count series by checking out sampled historical commits, running the metric tools, and writing snapshots into the going-forward store so those two trends have history.\n\n## Files\n- `scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py` — new: for sampled commits (default monthly), measure the tree and append snapshots via `src/rebar/metrics/snapshot.py`.\n  - **Complexity tool + parse:** `lizard <src_dir>` (cyclomatic complexity; already a project dependency-of-record for grounding, see `src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py`). Parse its per-function CCN and record `complexity` = the SUMMED cyclomatic complexity across all functions (an `int`).\n  - **Clone tool + parse:** `jscpd --reporters json --output <tmpdir> <src_dir>`; read `<tmpdir>/jscpd-report.json` and record `clone_count` = `statistics.total.clones` (the number of duplicated blocks, an `int`).\n  - **Measurement seam:** the per-commit measurement is a single function `measure_tree(tree_path) -> {\"complexity\": int, \"clone_count\": int}` that shells to the two tools; the test monkeypatches THIS function to return stub values, so the test needs neither `lizard` nor `jscpd` installed. A tool that is absent or errors makes `measure_tree` return `None` and the commit is skipped (logged, non-fatal).\n  - **`ts` MUST be the sampled commit's date**, not wall-clock: `write_snapshot(record, ts=<commit ISO date>, repo_root=...)` where the date is `git show -s --format=%cI <commit>` — otherwise every backfilled point would collapse onto the backfill-run time and the trend would be meaningless.\n- `tests/scripts/test_backfill_complexity_clone.py` — new.\n\n## Test tier\nThe test lives under `tests/scripts/` with `pytestmark = pytest.mark.scripts` (the scripts tier; `tests/unit/scripts/` does NOT exist). External tools are stubbed/mocked so the test is deterministic and needs no scc/lizard/jscpd installed.\n\n## Approach\nComplexity/clone are point-in-time; their movement needs seeded history, which git makes deterministic (checkout + tool run at each sampled commit). Writes through the same `snapshot.py` writer as the going-forward path so backfilled and live snapshots share one format; snapshots are labeled `source=snapshot, confidence=high` (deterministic tool output). Sampling cadence is a script arg (default monthly) — a stated default. This is an optional backfill script the core command does not depend on.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (temp git repo + stubbed tool output): the script writes one snapshot per sampled commit with the parsed complexity/clone numbers; a commit whose tool run fails is skipped and logged, not fatal.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/scripts/test_backfill_complexity_clone.py` passes (tier `scripts`): with `measure_tree` stubbed, sampling 3 fixture commits writes 3 snapshots, each containing integer `complexity` and `clone_count` keys, and each tagged with `ts` equal to its COMMIT's date (not the run time) — asserted by reading the snapshots back via `read_snapshots` and checking the per-commit `ts` and int-typed values.\n- [ ] a sampled commit whose `measure_tree` returns `None` (tool absent/errors) is skipped without aborting the backfill — test asserts the run continues and the other snapshots are still written.\n- [ ] every written snapshot carries `source=\"snapshot\"`, `confidence=\"high\"` — asserted.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"scripts/backfill_complexity_clone_snapshots.py","reason":"backfill script"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","3275-b164-2e9b-4e66"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"a301a0ed-5e4c-4493-b5b8-379e6e431726","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","backfill"],"ticket_id":"c595-9348-d4f2-4529","ticket_type":"task","title":"Backfill complexity/clone snapshots at sampled historical commits","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["70e7bbb0-fc45-4aec-a80c-29f0171b156e","8b00fcad-2b53-449a-ab61-a40196decb61","e02894f9-a982-48a4-8382-995a6f50ce05","0f1ea0ee-edbf-4ba9-b409-53c7a877e02e","00cd2bbb-b7ed-4822-8c17-0381ba2982c3","6bc3fd19-37d7-4665-abce-620bbbc2e9fe","a301a0ed-5e4c-4493-b5b8-379e6e431726","bd944ec6-ab7f-4043-8d17-8b326f6df242","830eddff-d796-4ed2-9a91-3c56649f47c4"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784453197910482976,"uuid":"0bc72311-1c0b-4d63-baa5-e6e80f3089b0"}